headlines.description: Mikal Bridges scored 20 points, Phil Booth added 17 points and six assists, and No. 1 Villanova made it look easy, beating DePaul 103-85 on Wednesday in the Big East opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores 20 as No. 1 Villanova pounds DePaul 103-85

video.headline: Villanova cruises against DePaul in Big East opener

headlines.description: Trevon Blueitt had 23 points, J.P. Macura scored 11 of his 15 points in the second half and No. 6 Xavier beat Marquette 91-87 on Wednesday night to survive a road test in its Big East opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 Xavier takes league opener, holds off Marquette 91-87

headlines.description: Frank Booker was 5 for 9 from 3-point range and scored 17 points to lead South Carolina to a 74-45 victory over Limestone on Wednesday.

headlines.description: Tyus Battle scored 22 points, including 10 in a row and 16 in the second half, and Paschal Chukwu had a career-high 15 points, 12 rebounds and five blocks to lead Syracuse to a 62-47 win over Eastern Michigan on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Battle, Chukwu lead Syracuse past Eastern Michigan, 62-47

headlines.description: E.C. Matthews found himself in the starting lineup and responded by scoring a season-high 20 points to lead Rhode Island to its third straight win, knocking off Florida Gulf Coast in the Rams' final nonconference game, 80-60 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Matthews sparks Rhode Island past Florida Gulf Coast, 80-60

headlines.description: Jarrod Simmons scored 12 points to lead five Pennsylvania players in double figures and the Quakers made 14 3-pointers in their 105-52 rout of Delaware State on Wednesday night.

Ben Lammers scored 22 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for his fourth double-double of the season and Josh Okogie scored 11 of his 13 points in the second night to help Georgia Tech beat Coppin State 76-62 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lammers, Okogie help Georgia Tech past Coppin State

headlines.description: Jaylen Barford scored 12 of his 19 points in the second half to help Arkansas put away CSU Bakersfield with a 95-68 win on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barford scores 19, Arkansas wins season-high 5th straight

headlines.description: Ethan Happ scored 18 points and grabbed 12 rebounds as Wisconsin beat Chicago State 82-70 on Wednesday in a closer-than-expected contest.
headlines.shortLinkText: Happ's double-double leads Wisconsin past Chicago State

headlines.description: Jarrey Foster and Shake Milton scored 14 points apiece to help SMU beat UCF 56-51 on Wednesday night in the American Athletic Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Foster, Milton help SMU beat UCF, extend home win streak

headlines.description: Joshua Braun scored 18 points and led five players in double-figure scoring as Grand Canyon blasted Morgan State, 100-74, to keep its undefeated run at Orleans Arena intact Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grand Canyon thumps Morgan State in Las Vegas, 100-74

headlines.description: Joe Furstinger dropped his third consecutive double-double and five other New Mexico players reached double figures as the Lobos beat Air Force 87-58 in their Mountain West opener Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Mexico outruns Air Force 87-58 behind Furstinger

headlines.description: Hayden Dalton scored 19 of his career-high 36 points in the second half to help Wyoming beat San Diego State 82-69 on Wednesday night in the Mountain West Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dalton scores 36, Wyoming beats San Diego St. in MW opener

headlines.description: Koby McEwen scored 24 points and Utah State opened its Mountain West Conference season by beating San Jose State for the 21st straight time, topping the Spartans 86-72 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah State tops San Jose State for 21st straight time, 86-72

headlines.description: Chandler Hutchison scored 24 points and Boise State never trailed in beating Colorado State 93-71 in the Mountain West Conference opener Wednesday night to notch the Broncos' eighth straight win at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise State downs Colorado State 93-71 behind Hutchison

headlines.description: Kendall Stephens scored 19 points, including five 3-pointers, and Caleb Martin had a double-double to help Nevada beat Fresno State 80-65 on Wednesday night in the Mountain West Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephens scores 19, Nevada beats Fresno State in MW opener

headlines.description: Tavrion Dawson poured in a career-high 33 points and Micheal Warren added a season-high 22 as CSU Northridge snapped an 11-game skid with a 93-63 win over NAIA San Diego Christian on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: CSU Northridge beats San Diego Christian, snaps 11-game skid

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
